	"2vANiZ4rWs" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#b6e3b6" WIDTH="150"><B>Rule</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">The Court held:\n\nThe fact that the<BR ALIGN='left'/>exchange by the shareholders of their<BR ALIGN='left'/>old shares for new was an incident of<BR ALIGN='left'/>the liquidation of the old corporation<BR ALIGN='left'/>did not deprive the exchange of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>character of a reorganization exchange,<BR ALIGN='left'/>which in truth it was. We know of no<BR ALIGN='left'/>rule of law which requires that a<BR ALIGN='left'/>reorganization, otherwise within any of<BR ALIGN='left'/>the definitions of section 112 (g) (1),<BR ALIGN='left'/>is not to be so regarded because it<BR ALIGN='left'/>occurs in the progress of a liquidation.</TD></TR>
