	Or2hGH0WKc [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#b6e3b6" WIDTH="150"><B>Rule</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">Section 112 (c) (2) is not applicable<BR ALIGN='left'/>unless the transaction falls within<BR ALIGN='left'/>section 112 (c) (1), which<BR ALIGN='left'/>provides:\n\nIf an exchange would be<BR ALIGN='left'/>within the provisions of subsection (b)<BR ALIGN='left'/>* * * (3) * * * of this section if it<BR ALIGN='left'/>were not for the fact that the property<BR ALIGN='left'/>received in exchange consists not only<BR ALIGN='left'/>of property permitted by such paragraph<BR ALIGN='left'/>* * * to be received without the<BR ALIGN='left'/>recognition of gain, but also of other<BR ALIGN='left'/>property or money, then the gain, if<BR ALIGN='left'/>any, to the recipient shall be<BR ALIGN='left'/>recognized, but in an amount not in<BR ALIGN='left'/>excess of the sum of such money and the<BR ALIGN='left'/>fair market value of such other<BR ALIGN='left'/>property.</TD></TR>
